{"type":"message","id":"5b61bdc9","parentId":"c5ff3db2","timestamp":"2026-03-03T13:56:39.008Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tasks directory is empty. So there are no pending tasks for Temujin currently. \n\nBut the user said Temujin isn't completing his tasks. Let me check if there are any task-related files elsewhere, or maybe check the cron jobs to see if there are any tasks scheduled for Temujin. \n\nActually, wait - let me re-read the user's question. They asked \"How come Temujin isn't completing his tasks?\" This implies there are tasks that should be getting done but aren't.\n\nLooking at the architecture:\n- The heartbeat daemon creates task files for temujin in `temujin/tasks/` when the LLM-powered context review identifies code generation needs\n- The architecture mentions that tasks are routed to Temujin when the Kublai context review finds code generation needs\n\nSince the task directory is empty, either:\n1. No tasks have been created for Temujin\n2. Tasks were completed and cleared\n\nLet me check the heartbeat log or any recent activity to see if there were any tasks assigned to Temujin that might have failed.\n\nActually, based on the architecture documentation, the issue might be that the 6 agents (Möngke, Chagatai, Temüjin, Jochi, Ögedei) don't actually run as separate OpenClaw sessions - they are simulated. The architecture mentions this is a \"Kurultai Architecture Gap\":\n\n> \"Heartbeats require Dashboard (web UI), not CLI\"\n> \"Continue with subagents until 10+ paying users\"\n> \"Upgrade Path: 0 users (subagents) → 10 users (persistent) → 100 users (6-agent config)\"\n\nSo Temujin might not be \"not completing tasks\" - it's that the full 6-agent system isn't fully implemented yet. Temujin tasks are handled through the heartbeat daemon's context review which creates task files, but the actual execution might not be happening.\n\nLet me summarize this for the user and explain the current architecture limitations.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"The `temujin/tasks/` directory is **empty** — no pending tasks are queued.\n\nHere's the issue: according to ARCHITECTURE.md, there's a **Kurultai Architecture Gap**:\n\n> *\"Heartbeats require Dashboard (web UI), not CLI\"*\n> *\"Continue with subagents until 10+ paying users\"*\n> *\"Upgrade Path: 0 users (subagents) → 10 users (persistent) → 100 users (6-agent config)\"*\n\n**Current state:**\n- **Kublai** runs as the main OpenClaw session ✅\n- The other 5 agents (Möngke, Chagatai, **Temüjin**, Jochi, Ögedei) are **simulated** through:\n  - Hourly reflection scripts\n  - The heartbeat daemon context review (creates task files in `temujin/tasks/`)\n  - Sub-agents when spawned\n\n**Temüjin specifically:**\n- The context review *should* create task files in `temujin/tasks/` when it detects code needs\n- But since the tasks directory is empty, either:\n  1. No code-generation needs were detected\n  2. The task creation/escalation pipeline isn't working\n\nWant me to dig into the heartbeat daemon logs to see if there's a failure in the task creation flow?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":143,"output":1097,"cacheRead":26120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27360,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772546185066}}
