{"type":"message","id":"363594e8","parentId":"9fce2156","timestamp":"2026-03-03T16:18:58.180Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to complete the next steps:\n1. Automate `sessions_spawn` calls for pending spawn requests (currently manual)\n2. Add cleanup for processed spawn request files\n\nI need to create a script that:\n1. Reads pending spawn requests from spawn-requests/*.md\n2. Calls sessions_spawn for each one\n3. Marks them as processed/cleaned up\n\nThe challenge is that sessions_spawn is an OpenClaw tool, not a CLI command. I have a few options:\n1. Create a cron job that calls sessions_spawn via the OpenClaw API\n2. Create a script that Kublai runs which uses sessions_spawn\n3. Modify the spawn-consumer to actually trigger the spawn\n\nSince we're in an OpenClaw session, I can create a script that gets called by cron and uses the sessions_spawn tool. But actually, the cleanest approach is to have Kublai periodically check for pending spawn requests and call sessions_spawn directly.\n\nLet me create a spawn-executor script that Kublai can run via cron to process pending spawn requests.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll automate the spawn execution and add cleanup. Let me create a spawn executor that Kublai runs via cron:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_54d5455853914323ad58e7f3","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/bin/bash\n# Spawn Executor - Reads pending spawn requests and executes sessions_spawn\n# Run every 2 minutes via cron\n# This script outputs spawn commands for Kublai to execute\n\nSPAWN_DIR=\"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/spawn-requests\"\nLOG_FILE=\"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/logs/spawn-executor.log\"\n\nmkdir -p \"$(dirname \"$LOG_FILE\")\"\n\nlog() {\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] $1\" | tee -a \"$LOG_FILE\"\n}\n\nlog \"=== Spawn Executor Cycle ===\"\n\nif [ ! -d \"$SPAWN_DIR\" ]; then\n    log \"No spawn requests directory found\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\n# Find pending spawn requests\nshopt -s nullglob\npending=(\"$SPAWN_DIR\"/*.md)\n\nif [ ${#pending[@]} -eq 0 ]; then\n    log \"No pending spawn requests\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\nlog \"Found ${#pending[@]} pending spawn request(s)\"\n\nfor request_file in \"${pending[@]}\"; do\n    # Skip if already processed\n    if [[ \"$request_file\" == *.processed.md ]] || [[ \"$request_file\" == *.executing.md ]]; then\n        continue\n    fi\n    \n    # Parse YAML frontmatter\n    agent=$(grep \"^agent:\" \"$request_file\" | cut -d: -f2 | tr -d ' ')\n    model=$(grep \"^model:\" \"$request_file\" | cut -d: -d: -f2 | tr -d ' ')\n    label=$(grep \"^label:\" \"$request_file\" | cut -d: -f2 | tr -d ' ')\n    task=$(grep \"^# Task:\" \"$request_file\" | sed 's/^# Task: //')\n    \n    if [ -z \"$agent\" ] || [ -z \"$task\" ]; then\n        log \"Invalid request file: $request_file\"\n        continue\n    fi\n    \n    log \"Spawning: $agent ($model) - $task\"\n    \n    # Mark as executing\n    mv \"$request_file\" \"${request_file%.md}.executing.md\"\n    \n    # Output the spawn command for Kublai to execute\n    # This gets picked up by the cron job which calls sessions_spawn\n    echo \"SPAWN_REQUEST:agent=$agent,model=$model,label=$label,task=$task\"\n    \ndone\n\nlog \"=== Cycle Complete ===\"\n","path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/spawn-executor.sh"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":113477,"output":1062,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114539,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772554688835}}
{"type":"message","id":"6cd8a892","parentId":"363594e8","timestamp":"2026-03-03T16:18:58.206Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_54d5455853914323ad58e7f3","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 1777 bytes to /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/spawn-executor.sh"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772554738197}}
{"type":"message","id":"47ec112a","parentId":"6cd8a892","timestamp":"2026-03-03T16:19:20.093Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to create a cron job that reads the spawn executor output and actually calls sessions_spawn. But since sessions_spawn is a tool, not a CLI command, I need a different approach.\n\nThe cleanest way is to have a cron job that:\n1. Runs the spawn executor\n2. Parses the output\n3. Uses OpenClaw's session spawning capability\n\nActually, looking at the cron system, it runs agentTurn messages. So I can create a cron job that tells Kublai to check for spawn requests and execute them.\n\nLet me create a simpler approach - a Python script that directly uses the OpenClaw sessions_spawn API or creates a message that triggers the spawn.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to have Kublai periodically check the spawn-requests directory and call sessions_spawn for each pending request. I can do this via a cron job that sends a message to Kublai.\n\nLet me create a cron job that runs every 2 minutes and tells Kublai to process spawn requests.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create the integration that actually calls sessions_spawn. I'll create a Python helper that Kublai's cron job can use:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fd57b17e1e7c46a894be9b0f","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nSpawn Request Processor - Reads pending spawn requests and outputs them for execution\nThis is called by Kublai's cron job which then calls sessions_spawn\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport json\nimport glob\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nSPAWN_DIR = \"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/spawn-requests\"\nLOG_FILE = \"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/logs/spawn-executor.log\"\n\ndef log(msg):\n    timestamp = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")\n    print(f\"[{timestamp}] {msg}\")\n    os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(LOG_FILE), exist_ok=True)\n    with open(LOG_FILE, 'a') as f:\n        f.write(f\"[{timestamp}] {msg}\\n\")\n\ndef parse_request_file(filepath):\n    \"\"\"Parse a spawn request markdown file\"\"\"\n    with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    \n    # Parse frontmatter\n    request = {}\n    lines = content.split('\\n')\n    in_frontmatter = False\n    \n    for line in lines:\n        if line.startswith('---'):\n            in_frontmatter = not in_frontmatter\n            continue\n        \n        if in_frontmatter and ':' in line:\n            key, value = line.split(':', 1)\n            request[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n        \n        if line.startswith('# Task:'):\n            request['task'] = line.replace('# Task:', '').strip()\n    \n    return request\n\ndef process_pending():\n    \"\"\"Process all pending spawn requests\"\"\"\n    log(\"=== Spawn Executor Cycle ===\")\n    \n    if not os.path.exists(SPAWN_DIR):\n        log(\"No spawn requests directory found\")\n        return []\n    \n    # Find pending requests\n    pending = glob.glob(f\"{SPAWN_DIR}/*.md\")\n    pending = [f for f in pending if not f.endswith('.processed.md') and not f.endswith('.executing.md')]\n    \n    if not pending:\n        log(\"No pending spawn requests\")\n        return []\n    \n    log(f\"Found {len(pending)} pending spawn request(s)\")\n    \n    spawn_requests = []\n    \n    for request_file in pending:\n        try:\n            request = parse_request_file(request_file)\n            \n            agent = request.get('agent', '')\n            model = request.get('model', 'qwen3.5-plus')\n            label = request.get('label', '')\n            task = request.get('task', '')\n            \n            if not agent or not task:\n                log(f\"Invalid request file: {request_file}\")\n                continue\n            \n            log(f\"Spawning: {agent} ({model}) - {task[:50]}...\")\n            \n            # Mark as executing\n            executing_file = request_file.replace('.md', '.executing.md')\n            os.rename(request_file, executing_file)\n            \n            spawn_requests.append({\n                'agent': agent,\n                'model': model,\n                'label': label,\n                'task': task,\n                'file': executing_file\n            })\n            \n        except Exception as e:\n            log(f\"Error processing {request_file}: {e}\")\n    \n    log(f\"=== Cycle Complete: {len(spawn_requests)} requests ===\")\n    return spawn_requests\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    requests = process_pending()\n    \n    # Output JSON for cron job to parse\n    if requests:\n        print(json.dumps({'spawn_requests': requests}, indent=2))\n    else:\n        print(json.dumps({'spawn_requests': []}))\n","path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/process-spawn-requests.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":114357,"output":1279,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115636,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772554738207}}
