{"type":"message","id":"3f0bd007","parentId":"900535f8","timestamp":"2026-03-03T16:19:27.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Spawn Consumer Report — 2026-03-03 11:19 AM**\n\n**Cycle Result:** No new agents spawned\n\n**Details:**\n- Spawn queue was empty (no pending requests)\n- No spawn-queue.jsonl file found at time of execution\n\n**Previously Spawned (from earlier cycle at 11:14 AM):**\n- Agent: temujin\n- Model: qwen3.5-plus\n- Task: Test spawning integration\n- Status: pending (spawn request file created)\n\n**Current Subagent Status:**\n- Active subagents: 0\n- Recent (last 30 min): 0\n\nThe spawn consumer script executed successfully but found no new spawn requests to process this cycle."}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772554767574}}
{"type":"message","id":"1eea04b6","parentId":"900535f8","timestamp":"2026-03-03T16:19:54.451Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to create a cron job that runs this script and then actually spawns the agents. The challenge is that the cron job runs in an isolated session, but sessions_spawn needs to be called from the main session.\n\nThe solution is to have the cron job send a message to the main session with the spawn requests, and then the main session can call sessions_spawn.\n\nActually, looking at the cron system more carefully - the cron job runs with payload.kind=\"agentTurn\" which means it runs an agent turn in an isolated session. But we want to spawn from the main session.\n\nLet me think about this differently. I can:\n1. Have the cron job run the process-spawn-requests.py script\n2. Have it send the results to the main session via sessions_send\n3. The main session then processes the spawn requests\n\nOr simpler: I can just have Kublai periodically check for spawn requests directly via a heartbeat task or cron job that runs in the main session.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to add a task to the heartbeat daemon that checks for spawn requests and calls sessions_spawn. But the heartbeat daemon is a separate Python process and can't call OpenClaw tools.\n\nLet me take a different approach: Create a cron job that runs in the main session context and processes spawn requests. I can use sessionTarget=\"main\" with a systemEvent payload that triggers Kublai to process spawns.\n\nWait, looking at the cron schema:\n- sessionTarget=\"main\" requires payload.kind=\"systemEvent\"\n- sessionTarget=\"isolated\" requires payload.kind=\"agentTurn\"\n\nSo I can create a cron job with sessionTarget=\"main\" that sends a systemEvent to Kublai telling him to process spawn requests. Then Kublai handles the actual spawning.\n\nLet me create that cron job.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me add a cron job that processes spawn requests in the main session:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ae51928d1a0f4f25a6c9976c","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"process-spawn-requests","schedule":{"kind":"every","everyMs":120000},"payload":{"kind":"systemEvent","text":"SPAWN_PROCESS: Check /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/spawn-requests/ for pending spawn requests and execute them via sessions_spawn"},"sessionTarget":"main","delivery":{"mode":"none"}}}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":115472,"output":898,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116370,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772554760119}}
