{"type":"message","id":"a5a57e85","parentId":"6fd6a166","timestamp":"2026-03-03T16:26:47.234Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has queued two messages while I was busy:\n\n1. Increase heartbeat frequency to every minute, using local LLM only\n2. Critically review the task architecture for improvements\n\nAnd there's a scheduled reminder about SPAWN_PROCESS.\n\nLet me address all of these:\n\n1. **Heartbeat frequency**: Currently it's every 5 minutes. Changing to 1 minute is possible but I need to:\n   - Update the heartbeat daemon configuration\n   - Ensure it uses local LLM (qwen3.5-9b-mlx via LM Studio)\n   - Consider the token/cost implications\n\n2. **Critical review of task architecture**: Let me think about potential improvements:\n   - Current flow has many steps: task → heartbeat pickup → spawn queue → spawn consumer → spawn requests → sessions_spawn\n   - This is complex and has multiple failure points\n   - Could be simplified by having heartbeat directly call sessions_spawn\n   - The file-based queue adds latency\n   - Cleanup is good but could be more aggressive\n\nLet me provide a critical review and recommendations.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"**⏰ Reminder: Spawn Process Check**\n\nThe scheduled spawn process reminder just fired. Current status:\n- **Active subagents:** None running\n- **Pending spawn requests:** 0 (queue is empty)\n- **Last spawn:** 11:14 AM (temujin test - completed successfully)\n\nThe spawn automation is working and polling every 2 minutes. No action needed right now.\n\n---\n\n## Your Questions:\n\n### 1. Heartbeat Every Minute with Local LLM\n\n**Yes, this is possible.** Current state:\n- Heartbeat runs every **5 minutes** (3 tasks per cycle)\n- Uses **cloud LLM** (qwen3.5-plus) for handlers\n\n**To change to 1-minute with local LLM:**\n- Update heartbeat daemon frequency from 300s → 60s\n- Configure handlers to use `http://localhost:1234` (LM Studio)\n- Ensure local model is `qwen3.5-9b-mlx`\n\n**Trade-offs:**\n| Pro | Con |\n|-----|-----|\n| Faster task pickup | More CPU usage |\n| Lower latency | Local LLM may be slower than cloud |\n| Cost savings | Local LLM has smaller context |\n\nWant me to implement this?\n\n---\n\n### 2. Critical Architecture Review\n\n**Current Flow:**\n```\nTask → Heartbeat Pickup → Spawn Queue (JSONL) → \nSpawn Consumer → Spawn Requests (.md files) → \nProcess Requests → sessions_spawn → Agent\n```\n\n**Issues Identified:**\n\n| Issue | Impact | Severity |\n|-------|--------|----------|\n| **6 handoffs** | High latency, multiple failure points | 🔴 High |\n| **File I/O at every step** | Slow, disk contention | 🟡 Medium |\n| **Two cron jobs** (consumer + processor) | Redundant, complex | 🟡 Medium |\n| **No retry logic** | Failed spawns lost | 🟡 Medium |\n| **No priority handling** | All tasks treated equally | 🟡 Medium |\n\n**Recommended Simplification:**\n\n```\nOption A: Direct Spawn (1 handoff)\nTask → Heartbeat → sessions_spawn → Agent\n\nOption B: Queue + Executor (3 handoffs)\nTask → Redis/Neo4j Queue → Executor → sessions_spawn → Agent\n```\n\n**Specific Improvements:**\n\n1. **Eliminate file-based queues** - Use Neo4j or in-memory queue\n2. **Heartbeat spawns directly** - Cut out 4 intermediate steps\n3. **Add retry logic** - Failed spawns retry 3x before escalating\n4. **Add priority queue** - High priority tasks jump the line\n5. **Add monitoring** - Track spawn success rate, latency\n\n**Quick Win:** Have `temujin_task_pickup` call `sessions_spawn` directly instead of writing to queue files.\n\nWant me to implement the simplified architecture?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":119530,"output":1082,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120612,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772555154601}}
