{"type":"message","id":"8854ee26","parentId":"c027c54e","timestamp":"2026-03-03T17:45:34.220Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if I've fully implemented all the cleanup actions I proposed. Let me check:\n\n1. ✅ Remove classify-task.py — I created kublai-task-router.py which integrates classification\n2. ✅ Kublai writes spawn-pending.json directly — kublai-task-router.py does this\n3. ⚠️ Add immediate spawn trigger — I call handle-spawns.py which processes the queue, but it doesn't actually call sessions_spawn. It just outputs \"READY_TO_SPAWN\" but nothing executes it.\n4. ✅ Keep heartbeat task_pickup — Already registered for all 6 agents\n\nThe gap is #3 - the spawn handler processes the queue but doesn't actually execute sessions_spawn. I need to either:\n- Have the handler output that Kublai can parse and then call sessions_spawn\n- Or have Kublai directly call sessions_spawn after writing to the queue\n\nLet me be honest about what's done and what's not, then complete the implementation.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"**Partially implemented.** Let me check what's complete:\n\n| Action | Status | Notes |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| ✅ Remove classify-task.py | Done | Created `kublai-task-router.py` |\n| ✅ Kublai writes spawn-pending.json directly | Done | Router writes queue |\n| ⚠️ Add immediate spawn trigger | **Incomplete** | Calls handle-spawns.py but it only outputs \"READY_TO_SPAWN\" - doesn't execute sessions_spawn |\n| ✅ Keep heartbeat task_pickup | Done | All 6 agents registered |\n\n**The Gap:** The spawn handler processes the queue but doesn't actually call `sessions_spawn`. It outputs what should be spawned, but nothing executes it.\n\n**Fix:** Have Kublai parse the output and call `sessions_spawn` immediately in the same cycle.\n\nLet me complete this now:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_16b6d321de824fe6a69c0aa3","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/kublai-task-router.py","oldText":"    # Call spawn handler to process immediately\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        [\"python3\", \"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/handle-spawns.py\"],\n        capture_output=True,\n        text=True,\n        timeout=30\n    )\n    \n    return {\n        \"agent\": classification[\"agent\"],\n        \"model\": classification[\"model\"],\n        \"label\": label,\n        \"task\": message.strip()[:100],\n        \"priority\": priority,\n        \"confidence\": round(classification[\"confidence\"], 2),\n        \"queued\": True,\n        \"spawn_output\": result.stdout.strip() if result.stdout else None\n    }","newText":"    # Mark as ready for spawn (status updated in queue)\n    with open(SPAWN_QUEUE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump({'spawns': existing, 'updated': time.time()}, f, indent=2)\n    \n    return {\n        \"agent\": classification[\"agent\"],\n        \"model\": classification[\"model\"],\n        \"label\": label,\n        \"task\": message.strip()[:100],\n        \"priority\": priority,\n        \"confidence\": round(classification[\"confidence\"], 2),\n        \"queued\": True,\n        \"ready_to_spawn\": True\n    }"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":140288,"output":935,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141223,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772559890040}}
