{"type":"message","id":"bad961a4","parentId":"9f9642b8","timestamp":"2026-03-03T18:01:05.468Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**✅ IMPLEMENTATION COMPLETE**\n\nAll three features implemented and tested:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Task Completion Feedback ✅\n\n**File:** `complete-task.py`\n\n**Usage:**\n```bash\npython3 complete-task.py <label> <status> [error]\n# Status: completed, failed, killed\n```\n\n**Flow:**\n- Agent finishes → calls `complete-task.py`\n- Updates `spawn-pending.json` status\n- Logs to `task-completions.jsonl`\n- Auto-cleanup after 1 hour\n\n**Tested:** ✅ mongke-1772559988 marked completed\n\n---\n\n### 2. Retry Logic (3x before dead letter) ✅\n\n**File:** `spawn-consumer.sh`\n\n**Features:**\n- Tracks `retry_count` per task\n- Auto-retries failed tasks (max 3)\n- Exhausted tasks → `spawn-dead-letter.json`\n- Preserves error messages\n\n**Queue Status Fields:**\n```json\n{\n  \"retry_count\": 0,\n  \"max_retries\": 3,\n  \"status\": \"ready|running|completed|failed\",\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```\n\n**Tested:** ✅ Retry tracking active\n\n---\n\n### 3. Continuous Task Support ✅\n\n**Files:** `chat_to_task.py`, `continuous_tasks.py`\n\n**Usage:**\n```python\nfrom chat_to_task import handle_chat_task\n\nresult = handle_chat_task(\n    \"Monitor Parse uptime\",\n    mode=\"session\",      # ← Persistent\n    continuous=True      # ← Never completes\n)\n```\n\n**Features:**\n- `mode=\"session\"` for never-ending tasks\n- `timeoutSeconds=0` (no timeout)\n- Skips re-spawning if already running\n- Heartbeat registry for built-in continuous tasks\n\n**Tested:** ✅ ogedei-1772560807 (continuous, session mode, running)\n\n---\n\n### Final Queue Status\n\n| Label | Agent | Status | Mode | Continuous | Retries |\n|-------|-------|--------|------|------------|---------|\n| mongke-1772559988 | mongke | ✅ completed | run | No | 0 |\n| ogedei-1772560807 | ogedei | 🟢 running | session | **Yes** | 0 |\n\n**Dead Letter:** Empty (no failures yet)  \n**Completions Logged:** 1"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772560865468}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7e66936","parentId":"40b8ceca","timestamp":"2026-03-03T18:01:28.335Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to add Neo4j task tracking with queryable history, and integrate it with the hourly Kurultai reflections. Let me think about the best approach:\n\n1. **Neo4j Schema for Tasks:**\n   - Task nodes with properties (label, agent, status, created, completed, etc.)\n   - Relationships: (:Agent)-[:EXECUTED]->(:Task), (:Task)-[:DEPENDS_ON]->(:Task)\n   - Track: spawn events, completion events, retries, errors\n\n2. **Integration Points:**\n   - `chat_to_task.py` - Write to Neo4j when task created\n   - `spawn-consumer.sh` - Update Neo4j when task spawned\n   - `complete-task.py` - Update Neo4j when task completed\n   - Hourly reflections - Query Neo4j for task history/metrics\n\n3. **Hourly Reflection Integration:**\n   - Query tasks completed in last hour\n   - Query success/failure rates\n   - Query agent workload distribution\n   - Include in reflection report\n\nLet me implement this step by step.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll implement Neo4j task tracking with queryable history and integrate it into hourly reflections.\n\n## 1. Neo4j Task Schema + Tracker\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f6ea08e7c19e47ca80f690d1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nNeo4j Task Tracker - Persistent task history with queryable metrics\n\nSchema:\n- (:Task {label, agent, status, created, completed, ...})\n- (:Agent {name})-[:EXECUTED]->(:Task)\n- (:Task)-[:RETRIED]->(:Task)\n\nUsage:\n    from neo4j_task_tracker import TaskTracker\n    tracker = TaskTracker()\n    tracker.create_task(\"mongke-123\", \"mongke\", \"Research X\")\n    tracker.update_status(\"mongke-123\", \"completed\")\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom neo4j import GraphDatabase\n\nclass TaskTracker:\n    def __init__(self):\n        uri = os.getenv(\"NEO4J_URI\", \"bolt://localhost:7687\")\n        user = os.getenv(\"NEO4J_USER\", \"neo4j\")\n        password = os.getenv(\"NEO4J_PASSWORD\", \"myStrongPassword123\")\n        \n        self.driver = GraphDatabase.driver(uri, auth=(user, password))\n        \n    def close(self):\n        self.driver.close()\n    \n    def create_task(self, label, agent, task_desc, priority=\"normal\", \n                    mode=\"run\", continuous=False, source=\"chat\"):\n        \"\"\"Create a task node\"\"\"\n        with self.driver.session() as session:\n            session.run(\"\"\"\n                MERGE (a:Agent {name: $agent})\n                CREATE (t:Task {\n                    label: $label,\n                    agent: $agent,\n                    task: $task,\n                    priority: $priority,\n                    mode: $mode,\n                    continuous: $continuous,\n                    source: $source,\n                    status: 'ready',\n                    created: datetime(),\n                    retry_count: 0,\n                    max_retries: 3\n                })\n                CREATE (a)-[:EXECUTED]->(t)\n            \"\"\",\n            label=label, agent=agent, task=task_desc,\n            priority=priority, mode=mode, continuous=continuous, source=source)\n    \n    def update_status(self, label, status, error=None, session_key=None):\n        \"\"\"Update task status\"\"\"\n        with self.driver.session() as session:\n            session.run(\"\"\"\n                MATCH (t:Task {label: $label})\n                SET t.status = $status,\n                    t.updated = datetime()\n                \"\"\",\n                label=label, status=status)\n            \n            if status == 'running' and session_key:\n                session.run(\"\"\"\n                    MATCH (t:Task {label: $label})\n                    SET t.session_key = $session_key,\n                        t.started = datetime()\n                \"\"\", label=label, session_key=session_key)\n            \n            if status in ['completed', 'failed', 'killed']:\n                session.run(\"\"\"\n                    MATCH (t:Task {label: $label})\n                    SET t.completed = datetime()\n                \"\"\", label=label)\n            \n            if error:\n                session.run(\"\"\"\n                    MATCH (t:Task {label: $label})\n                    SET t.error = $error\n                \"\"\", label=label, error=error)\n    \n    def increment_retry(self, label):\n        \"\"\"Increment retry count\"\"\"\n        with self.driver.session() as session:\n            session.run(\"\"\"\n                MATCH (t:Task {label: $label})\n                SET t.retry_count = t.retry_count + 1,\n                    t.last_retry = datetime()\n            \"\"\", label=label)\n    \n    def get_tasks_by_agent(self, agent, limit=10):\n        \"\"\"Get recent tasks for an agent\"\"\"\n        with self.driver.session() as session:\n            result = session.run(\"\"\"\n                MATCH (a:Agent {name: $agent})-[:EXECUTED]->(t:Task)\n                RETURN t ORDER BY t.created DESC LIMIT $limit\n            \"\"\", agent=agent, limit=limit)\n            return [dict(r['t']) for r in result]\n    \n    def get_tasks_by_status(self, status, limit=50):\n        \"\"\"Get tasks by status\"\"\"\n        with self.driver.session() as session:\n            result = session.run(\"\"\"\n                MATCH (t:Task {status: $status})\n                RETURN t ORDER BY t.created DESC LIMIT $limit\n            \"\"\", status=status, limit=limit)\n            return [dict(r['t']) for r in result]\n    \n    def get_hourly_summary(self, hours=1):\n        \"\"\"Get task summary for last N hours\"\"\"\n        with self.driver.session() as session:\n            result = session.run(\"\"\"\n                MATCH (t:Task)\n                WHERE t.created > datetime() - duration('PT' + $hours + 'H')\n                RETURN \n                    t.agent AS agent,\n                    count(t) AS total,\n                    sum(CASE WHEN t.status = 'completed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS completed,\n                    sum(CASE WHEN t.status = 'failed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS failed,\n                    sum(CASE WHEN t.status = 'running' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS running,\n                    sum(CASE WHEN t.status = 'ready' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS ready,\n                    avg(CASE WHEN t.completed IS NOT NULL \n                        THEN duration.between(t.created, t.completed).seconds \n                        ELSE null END) AS avg_duration_seconds\n                GROUP BY t.agent\n                ORDER BY total DESC\n            \"\"\", hours=hours)\n            return [dict(r) for r in result]\n    \n    def get_completion_rate(self, hours=24):\n        \"\"\"Get success/failure rates\"\"\"\n        with self.driver.session() as session:\n            result = session.run(\"\"\"\n                MATCH (t:Task)\n                WHERE t.created > datetime() - duration('PT' + $hours + 'H')\n                  AND t.status IN ['completed', 'failed']\n                WITH \n                    count(t) AS total,\n                    sum(CASE WHEN t.status = 'completed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS success\n                RETURN \n                    total,\n                    success,\n                    round(100.0 * success / total, 1) AS success_rate\n            \"\"\", hours=hours)\n            record = result.single()\n            return dict(record) if record else {}\n    \n    def get_continuous_tasks(self):\n        \"\"\"Get all running continuous tasks\"\"\"\n        with self.driver.session() as session:\n            result = session.run(\"\"\"\n                MATCH (t:Task {continuous: true, status: 'running'})\n                RETURN t ORDER BY t.created DESC\n            \"\"\")\n            return [dict(r['t']) for r in result]\n    \n    def get_reflection_data(self, agent=None, hours=1):\n        \"\"\"Get data for hourly reflection\"\"\"\n        with self.driver.session() as session:\n            if agent:\n                result = session.run(\"\"\"\n                    MATCH (a:Agent {name: $agent})-[:EXECUTED]->(t:Task)\n                    WHERE t.created > datetime() - duration('PT' + $hours + 'H')\n                    RETURN \n                        count(t) AS total_tasks,\n                        sum(CASE WHEN t.status = 'completed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS completed,\n                        sum(CASE WHEN t.status = 'failed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS failed,\n                        sum(t.retry_count) AS total_retries,\n                        avg(CASE WHEN t.completed IS NOT NULL \n                            THEN duration.between(t.created, t.completed).seconds \n                            ELSE null END) AS avg_duration\n                    \"\"\", agent=agent, hours=hours)\n            else:\n                result = session.run(\"\"\"\n                    MATCH (t:Task)\n                    WHERE t.created > datetime() - duration('PT' + $hours + 'H')\n                    RETURN \n                        count(t) AS total_tasks,\n                        sum(CASE WHEN t.status = 'completed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS completed,\n                        sum(CASE WHEN t.status = 'failed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS failed,\n                        sum(t.retry_count) AS total_retries\n                    \"\"\", hours=hours)\n            \n            record = result.single()\n            return dict(record) if record else {}\n\n\n# Singleton instance\n_tracker = None\n\ndef get_tracker():\n    \"\"\"Get or create tracker instance\"\"\"\n    global _tracker\n    if _tracker is None:\n        _tracker = TaskTracker()\n    return _tracker\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    # Test\n    tracker = get_tracker()\n    print(\"Neo4j Task Tracker initialized\")\n    print(\"Hourly summary:\", tracker.get_hourly_summary(1))\n    tracker.close()\n","path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/neo4j_task_tracker.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":164415,"output":2454,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":166869,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772560864618}}
