{"type":"message","id":"ebf54262","parentId":"8a0312a8","timestamp":"2026-03-03T18:10:23.526Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tasks are correctly marked as running/completed. The system is working as designed. Let me provide a clear summary to the user.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"**✅ System is Working Correctly**\n\n**Queue Status:**\n- `mongke-1772559988`: ✅ **Completed** (finished at 1:00 PM)\n- `ogedei-1772560807`: 🟢 **Running** (continuous uptime monitor)\n- `jochi-1772560963`: 🟢 **Running** (test task)\n\n**Why They're Not Being Re-Spawned:**\n1. **Completed tasks** → Cleaned up after 1 hour (auto-cleanup)\n2. **Running tasks** → Already executing, no need to spawn again\n3. **Continuous tasks** → Skipped if already running (prevents infinite spawning)\n\n**The spawn consumer logic:**\n```python\n# Only spawns \"ready\" status\nif s.get('status') == 'ready':\n    spawn()\n\n# Skips continuous tasks already running\nif continuous and s.get('session_key'):\n    skip()  # Already running\n```\n\n**This is correct behavior.** The queue is not a backlog — it's a **status tracker**. Tasks flow through:\n```\nready → running → completed → (auto-cleanup after 1h)\n```\n\n**Want to test with a NEW task?** I can create one and watch it spawn immediately."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":184086,"output":353,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":184439,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772561417833}}
