{"type":"message","id":"43d32b5d","parentId":"72a3c5ca","timestamp":"2026-03-03T18:14:45.593Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking for two improvements:\n1. Clean up completed tasks immediately once finished (not wait 1 hour)\n2. Move continuous tasks to a separate tracking mechanism (not in the main queue)\n\nThese are good suggestions - the queue should be for pending/active work, not historical data. Let me implement both.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"**Yes to both!** Let me implement:\n\n1. **Immediate cleanup of completed tasks** (don't wait 1 hour)\n2. **Separate continuous task registry** (not in main queue)\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c5fa859dcf944bb999550c75","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/spawn-consumer.sh","oldText":"# Cleanup completed spawns older than 1 hour\ncutoff = datetime.now().timestamp() - 3600\nspawns = [s for s in spawns if \n          s.get('status') not in ['completed', 'failed'] or\n          s.get('completed_at') is None or\n          datetime.fromisoformat(s.get('completed_at', '2000-01-01')).timestamp() > cutoff]","newText":"# Immediate cleanup of completed/failed tasks (keep only running/ready)\nspawns = [s for s in spawns if s.get('status') in ['ready', 'running']]"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":177277,"output":377,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":177654,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772561611937}}
