{"type":"message","id":"e4c2983f","parentId":"70312e3c","timestamp":"2026-03-03T18:27:05.226Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me make the chat_log_analyzer.py executable and test the integrated system.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_541267dda4bc4ae1bca226dd","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"chmod +x /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts/chat_log_analyzer.py\n\n# Test integrated meta-reflection with chat review\necho \"=== Test: Meta-Reflection with Chat Review ===\" \ncd /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/scripts\npython3 meta_reflection.py --agent temujin --hours 1 --chat-review --chat-hours 2 2>&1 | head -60\n\n# Commit\ncd /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main && git add -A && git commit -m \"[feature] Chat log review integrated into meta-reflections\n\nINTEGRATED:\n1. Chat Log Analyzer (chat_log_analyzer.py)\n   - Extracts sessions from last N hours\n   - Identifies system interactions (task, spawn, agent keywords)\n   - Detects potential issues (errors, failures)\n   - Provides ARCHITECTURE.md context\n   - Generates critical evaluation questions\n\n2. Meta-Reflection Integration\n   - meta_reflection.py: --chat-review flag enables chat analysis\n   - Chat review appears BEFORE metrics in reflection\n   - Agents see both quantitative (metrics) and qualitative (chat) data\n   - Single unified feedback submission to Kublai\n\n3. Hourly Reflection Update\n   - Each agent reviews: 1hr metrics + 2hr chat logs\n   - Chat insights inform system evaluation\n   - Architecture alignment check included\n   - Direct Kublai review workflow documented\n\nWORKFLOW (No Redundancy):\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ Hourly Reflection Trigger           │\n└──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n               │\n        ┌──────▼───────┐\n        │ Agent Runs   │\n        │ Reflection   │\n        └──────┬───────┘\n               │\n    ┌──────────┼──────────┐\n    │    