{"type":"message","id":"3efed01e","parentId":"731c9504","timestamp":"2026-03-03T19:08:19.032Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about what heartbeat tasks can be moved to the local LLM (LM Studio running qwen3.5-9b-mlx) instead of using cloud LLMs. This is a good optimization question for cost reduction and latency.\n\nLet me think about which tasks are good candidates for local LLM:\n\nGood candidates for local LLM:\n1. Simple classification/routing tasks\n2. Tasks that don't need massive context\n3. Tasks where speed matters more than perfect accuracy\n4. Routine monitoring/checking tasks\n5. Tasks that run frequently (5-min intervals)\n\nGood candidates for cloud LLM:\n1. Complex reasoning tasks\n2. Tasks needing large context windows\n3. Critical decisions (Kublai review)\n4. Creative writing (Chagatai content)\n5. Tasks where accuracy is paramount\n\nLet me identify specific tasks that could move to local:\n\nFrom the heartbeat daemon tasks:\n- task_pickup (all agents) - Simple file polling, minimal LLM needed\n- health_check (ogedei) - System status, could be local\n- memory_curation_rapid (jochi) - Token budget enforcement, could be local\n- status_synthesis (kublai) - Might need cloud for good synthesis\n- smoke_tests (jochi) - Could be local\n- file_consistency (ogedei) - Could be local\n\nFrom the reflection system:\n- Task metrics from Neo4j - No LLM needed (direct DB queries)\n- Chat log analysis - Could be local (pattern matching)\n- Meta-reflection generation - Should stay cloud (needs reasoning)\n\nLet me provide a practical answer about what can move to local.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes! Several heartbeat tasks can move to the local LLM (LM Studio, qwen3.5-9b-mlx) for **cost savings** and **lower latency**.\n\n## Tasks That Can Move to Local LLM\n\n### ✅ High Confidence (Move to Local)\n\n| Task | Agent | Frequency | Why Local Works |\n|------|-------|-----------|-----------------|\n| **task_pickup** (all 6 agents) | All | 5 min | Simple file polling, minimal reasoning |\n| **health_check** | ogedei | 5 min | System status checks (Neo4j, disk, gateway) |\n| **memory_curation_rapid** | jochi | 5 min | Token budget enforcement (rule-based) |\n| **file_consistency** | ogedei | 15 min | File comparison (deterministic) |\n| **smoke_tests** | jochi | 15 min | Quick tests (pass/fail) |\n| **status_synthesis** | kublai | 5 min | Status aggregation (can be local) |\n\n**Estimated savings:** ~60% of heartbeat LLM calls\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Medium Confidence (Test First)\n\n| Task | Agent | Frequency | Considerations |\n|------|-------|-----------|----------------|\n| **content_generation** | chagatai | 60 min | Test quality vs cloud |\n| **quick_research** | mongke | 60 min | Local can summarize, may need cloud for depth |\n| **reflection_consolidation** | chagatai | 30 min | Test coherence |\n\n---\n\n### ❌ Keep on Cloud\n\n| Task | Agent | Frequency | Why Cloud Needed |\n|------|-------|-----------|------------------|\n| **kublai_review** | kublai | 60 min | Critical decisions, needs full context |\n| **meta-reflection** (all agents) | All | 60 min | Complex reasoning, system evaluation |\n| **chat_to_task classification** | kublai | On-demand | Accuracy critical for routing |\n| **deep_curation** | jochi | 360 min | Complex memory analysis |\n| **knowledge_gap_analysis** | mongke | 1440 min | Needs broad knowledge |\n| **validate_improvements** | system | 60 min | Critical validation |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Move Obvious Tasks (Week 1)\n\n**Files to modify:**\n- `/Users/kublai/kurultai/kublai-repo/tools/kurultai/agent_tasks.py`\n\n**Changes:**\n```python\n# Current (cloud)\nCLOUD_LLM_MODEL = \"qwen3.5-plus\"\n\n# Add local routing\nLOCAL_LLM_URL = \"http://localhost:1234/v1/chat/completions\"\nLOCAL_LLM_MODEL = \"qwen3.5-9b-mlx\"\n\n# Tasks to route to local\nLOCAL_TASKS = [\n    \"task_pickup\",      # All 6 agents\n    \"health_check\",     # ogedei\n    \"memory_curation_rapid\",  # jochi\n    \"file_consistency\", # ogedei\n    \"smoke_tests\",      # jochi\n]\n\ndef get_model_for_task(agent, task_name):\n    if task_name in LOCAL_TASKS:\n        return LOCAL_LLM_MODEL\n    return CLOUD_LLM_MODEL\n```\n\n**Expected impact:**\n- **Latency:** 12s → 3s (75% faster)\n- **Cost:** $0.02/call → $0 (free)\n- **Quality:** ~95% of cloud (acceptable for routine tasks)\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Test Medium Confidence (Week 2)\n\nRun A/B tests:\n- Run content_generation on local for 1 week\n- Compare quality vs cloud\n- If >90% quality → move to local\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Hybrid Routing (Week 3)\n\nImplement smart fallback:\n```python\ndef run_with_fallback(task, local_first=True):\n    if local_first:\n        try:\n            result = call_local_llm(task, timeout=10)\n            if result.confidence > 0.8:\n                return result\n        except:\n            pass\n    \n    # Fallback to cloud\n    return call_cloud_llm(task)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Quick Win: Task Pickup (5-min tasks)\n\n**Current:** All 6 agents → cloud LLM  \n**After:** All 6 agents → local LLM\n\n**Math:**\n- 6 agents × 12 cycles/hour × 24 hours = **1,728 calls/day**\n- Cloud cost: ~$0.02/call = **$34.56/day**\n- Local cost: **$0/day**\n- **Savings: ~$1,000/month**\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Action\n\nWant me to implement **Phase 1** now? I can:\n\n1. Add local LLM routing to `agent_tasks.py`\n2. Configure heartbeat daemon to use local for routine tasks\n3. Add fallback to cloud if local fails\n4. Add metrics tracking (local success rate, latency)\n\nThis would immediately reduce LLM costs by ~60% while maintaining quality for critical tasks."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":232453,"output":1900,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":234353,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772564876219}}
{"type":"message","id":"0eb74739","parentId":"3efed01e","timestamp":"2026-03-03T19:08:20.758Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes! Several heartbeat tasks can move to the local LLM (LM Studio, qwen3.5-9b-mlx) for **cost savings** and **lower latency**.\n\n## Tasks That Can Move to Local LLM\n\n### ✅ High Confidence (Move to Local)\n\n| Task | Agent | Frequency | Why Local Works |\n|------|-------|-----------|-----------------|\n| **task_pickup** (all 6 agents) | All | 5 min | Simple file polling, minimal reasoning |\n| **health_check** | ogedei | 5 min | System status checks (Neo4j, disk, gateway) |\n| **memory_curation_rapid** | jochi | 5 min | Token budget enforcement (rule-based) |\n| **file_consistency** | ogedei | 15 min | File comparison (deterministic) |\n| **smoke_tests** | jochi | 15 min | Quick tests (pass/fail) |\n| **status_synthesis** | kublai | 5 min | Status aggregation (can be local) |\n\n**Estimated savings:** ~60% of heartbeat LLM calls\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Medium Confidence (Test First)\n\n| Task | Agent | Frequency | Considerations |\n|------|-------|-----------|----------------|\n| **content_generation** | chagatai | 60 min | Test quality vs cloud |\n| **quick_research** | mongke | 60 min | Local can summarize, may need cloud for depth |\n| **reflection_consolidation** | chagatai | 30 min | Test coherence |\n\n---\n\n### ❌ Keep on Cloud\n\n| Task | Agent | Frequency | Why Cloud Needed |\n|------|-------|-----------|------------------|\n| **kublai_review** | kublai | 60 min | Critical decisions, needs full context |\n| **meta-reflection** (all agents) | All | 60 min | Complex reasoning, system evaluation |\n| **chat_to_task classification** | kublai | On-demand | Accuracy critical for routing |\n| **deep_curation** | jochi | 360 min | Complex memory analysis |\n| **knowledge_gap_analysis** | mongke | 1440 min | Needs broad knowledge |\n| **validate_improvements** | system | 60 min | Critical validation |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Move Obvious Tasks (Week 1)\n\n**Files to modify:**\n- `/Users/kublai/kurultai/kublai-repo/tools/kurultai/agent_tasks.py`\n\n**Changes:**\n```python\n# Current (cloud)\nCLOUD_LLM_MODEL = \"qwen3.5-plus\"\n\n# Add local routing\nLOCAL_LLM_URL = \"http://localhost:1234/v1/chat/completions\"\nLOCAL_LLM_MODEL = \"qwen3.5-9b-mlx\"\n\n# Tasks to route to local\nLOCAL_TASKS = [\n    \"task_pickup\",      # All 6 agents\n    \"health_check\",     # ogedei\n    \"memory_curation_rapid\",  # jochi\n    \"file_consistency\", # ogedei\n    \"smoke_tests\",      # jochi\n]\n\ndef get_model_for_task(agent, task_name):\n    if task_name in LOCAL_TASKS:\n        return LOCAL_LLM_MODEL\n    return CLOUD_LLM_MODEL\n```\n\n**Expected impact:**\n- **Latency:** 12s → 3s (75% faster)\n- **Cost:** $0.02/call → $0 (free)\n- **Quality:** ~95% of cloud (acceptable for routine tasks)\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Test Medium Confidence (Week 2)\n\nRun A/B tests:\n- Run content_generation on local for 1 week\n- Compare quality vs cloud\n- If >90% quality → move to local\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Hybrid Routing (Week 3)\n\nImplement smart fallback:\n```python\ndef run_with_fallback(task, local_first=True):\n    if local_first:\n        try:\n            result = call_local_llm(task, timeout=10)\n            if result.confidence > 0.8:\n                return result\n        except:\n            pass\n    \n    # Fallback to cloud\n    return call_cloud_llm(task)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Quick Win: Task Pickup (5-min tasks)\n\n**Current:** All 6 agents → cloud LLM  \n**After:** All 6 agents → local LLM\n\n**Math:**\n- 6 agents × 12 cycles/hour × 24 hours = **1,728 calls/day**\n- Cloud cost: ~$0.02/call = **$34.56/day**\n- Local cost: **$0/day**\n- **Savings: ~$1,000/month**\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Action\n\nWant me to implement **Phase 1** now? I can:\n\n1. Add local LLM routing to `agent_tasks.py`\n2. Configure heartbeat daemon to use local for routine tasks\n3. Add fallback to cloud if local fails\n4. Add metrics tracking (local success rate, latency)\n\nThis would immediately reduce LLM costs by ~60% while maintaining quality for critical tasks."}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772564900758}}
