{"type":"message","id":"d129d926","parentId":"f3202bcb","timestamp":"2026-03-03T19:34:03.965Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if I'm there. I've been responding with spawn consumer reports which are automated messages, but the user is asking if I (Kublai) am present and responsive. I should respond directly to acknowledge I'm here and address their earlier request about Phase 1 local LLM implementation that they noted wasn't completed.\n\nLet me acknowledge I'm here and provide a status update on what's been done and what still needs to be done for Phase 1.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes, I'm here! \n\n**Status Update on Phase 1 (Local LLM Integration):**\n\nI've created the infrastructure but haven't fully integrated it yet. Here's what's done vs. what's pending:\n\n## ✅ Completed\n\n1. **Local LLM Router** (`local_llm_router.py`)\n   - Routes tasks to local LLM (qwen3.5-9b-mlx)\n   - Cloud fallback on failure\n   - Metrics tracking (success rate, latency)\n   - Ready to use\n\n2. **Heartbeat Task Analyzer** (`heartbeat_task_analyzer.py`)\n   - Reviews each agent's heartbeat tasks\n   - Identifies local LLM candidates\n   - Generates recommendations to Kublai\n   - Integrated into hourly reflections\n\n3. **Meta-Reflection Integration**\n   - Agents now review heartbeat tasks during reflections\n   - Submit feedback to Kublai via Neo4j\n   - Kublai can approve → create tasks\n\n## ⏳ Still Pending\n\n1. **Update heartbeat task handlers** to actually call `run_with_routing()` instead of direct cloud calls\n2. **Test local LLM** is running and accessible at `localhost:1234`\n3. **Verify metrics logging** is working\n\n## Quick Test\n\nLet me verify the local LLM router is working:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a8f546fa13bd49d08da89fe4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test local LLM connectivity\necho \"=== Testing Local LLM ===\" \ncurl -s http://localhost:1234/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"model\": \"qwen3.5-9b-mlx\", \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}], \"max_tokens\": 10}' | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('Local LLM:', '✅ Working' if d.get('choices') else '❌ Error:', d)\" 2>&1 | head -5\n\n# Test metrics summary\necho \"\" && echo \"=== Local LLM Metrics ===\" \npython3 /Users/kublai/kurultai/kublai-repo/tools/kurultai/local_llm_router.py --metrics --hours 24 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":253430,"output":695,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":254125,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772566389031}}
