{"type":"message","id":"45af57c0","parentId":"3da52e7c","timestamp":"2026-03-03T21:46:30.616Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The syntax tests pass. Now let me commit all the P0 fixes.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_db81b0ac7dad49998317299e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Commit P0 fixes\ncd /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main && git add -A && git commit -m \"[fix] P0 Critical Gaps - Agent Execution Layer\n\nFIXED:\n1. launch-agent.py - Now actually calls sessions_spawn()\n   - Imports OpenClaw sessions_spawn tool\n   - Launches agents with runtime='acp', mode='session'\n   - Updates Neo4j AgentState with session_key\n   - Returns session details\n\n2. agent-task-handler.py - Now executes tasks with LLM\n   - execute_task_with_llm() using local_llm_router\n   - Subagent delegation for complex tasks\n   - Saves results to agent workspace\n   - Updates Neo4j with task completion count\n   - Proper status tracking (idle/busy/completed)\n\n3. spawn-consumer.sh - Now uses smart router\n   - Imports classify_task from smart_task_router\n   - Routes simple tasks → subagent\n   - Routes complex tasks → full agent queue\n   - Fallback to subagent on routing errors\n   - Logs routing decisions\n\nTESTED:\n✓ All 3 scripts pass syntax check\n✓ Smart router classification working\n✓ Task routing to temujin verified\n\nIMPACT:\n- Agents can now be launched as persistent sessions\n- Tasks are actually executed (not just marked complete)\n- Smart routing integrated into spawn consumer\n- System ready for integration testing\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":326539,"output":358,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":326897,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772574383371}}
