{"type":"message","id":"3b2ed381","parentId":"905a1aed","timestamp":"2026-03-03T23:41:39.117Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"b864035f-66b5-4b4f-9339-70aa5318a4f3\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"sender\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-03 18:41 EST] verify whether individual agents are actually completing tasks (like temujin) or if it's kublai actualy doing it"}],"timestamp":1772581299108}}
{"type":"message","id":"71db6438","parentId":"3b2ed381","timestamp":"2026-03-03T23:41:58.363Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to verify whether the individual agents (like Temujin) are actually executing tasks, or if Kublai is doing all the work. This is an important architectural question - we built all this infrastructure for persistent agents, but we need to verify it's actually working as designed.\n\nLet me check:\n1. Task completion logs - which agent is marked as completing tasks\n2. Neo4j AgentState - are individual agents showing tasks_completed increments\n3. Workspace files - are tasks being saved to individual agent workspaces\n4. Task queue status - are tasks being picked up by individual agents or just processed by Kublai\n\nThis is a critical verification because if Kublai is doing all the work, then the hybrid architecture isn't actually providing the benefits we designed it for.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_60cfd2a2ca9f4969bdf1b444","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Verify which agents are actually completing tasks\necho \"=== Verifying Agent Task Execution ===\" \n\n# 1. Check Neo4j for tasks_completed by agent\necho \"1. Neo4j AgentState - Tasks Completed:\"\npython3 -c \"\nfrom neo4j import GraphDatabase\ndriver = GraphDatabase.driver('bolt://localhost:7687', auth=('neo4j', 'myStrongPassword123'))\nwith driver.session() as session:\n    result = session.run('MATCH (a:AgentState) RETURN a.name AS name, a.tasks_completed AS completed ORDER BY a.name')\n    print('Agent | Tasks Completed')\n    print('-' * 30)\n    for r in result:\n        print(f'{r[\\\"name\\\"]:<12} | {r[\\\"completed\\\"] or 0}')\ndriver.close()\n\" 2>&1 | head -15\n\n# 2. Check task completion logs\necho \"\" && echo \"2. Task Completion Logs:\"\ntail -20 /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/logs/task-completions.jsonl 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        print(f\\\"{d.get('completed_at', '?')[:19]} | {d.get('label', '?'):<25} | {d.get('status', '?')}\\\")\n    except:\n        pass\n\" 2>&1 | head -10\n\n# 3. Check agent workspaces for task results\necho \"\" && echo \"3. Agent Workspace Task Results:\"\nfor agent in temujin mongke chagatai jochi ogedei; do\n    count=$(ls /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/$agent/workspace/task-*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    echo \"  $agent: $count task results\"\ndone\n\n# 4. Check task queues (pending vs completed)\necho \"\" && echo \"4. Task Queue Status:\"\nfor agent in temujin mongke chagatai jochi ogedei kublai; do\n    pending=$(ls /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/$agent/tasks/*.md 2>/dev/null | grep -v executing | grep -v done | wc -l)\n    executing=$(ls /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/$agent/tasks/*.executing.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    done=$(ls /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/$agent/tasks/*.done.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l)\n    echo \"  $agent: $pending pending, $executing executing, $done completed\"\ndone\n\n# 5. Check who's processing tasks (cron logs)\necho \"\" && echo \"5. Recent Cron Activity:\"\ntail -10 /Users/kublai/.openclaw/agents/main/logs/task-consumer.log 2>/dev/null || echo \"  No task-consumer.log entries\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":364993,"output":1023,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":366016,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772581299114}}
