{"type":"message","id":"148b4b62","parentId":"78128a84","timestamp":"2026-03-04T00:43:50.093Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway is detecting conflicts with other LaunchAgents (heartbeat-watchdog, spawn-consumer) that I created. These aren't actually gateway conflicts - they're just other services. But the gateway is complaining about them.\n\nThe logs show:\n- Gateway is running (pid 95821, state active)\n- It's detecting other LaunchAgents and warning about conflicts\n- The warnings are about ai.openclaw.heartbeat-watchdog and ai.openclaw.spawn-consumer\n\nThese aren't actual gateway conflicts - they're different services. But the gateway status check is flagging them as \"gateway-like services\".\n\nThe fix is to either:\n1. Remove the ai.openclaw.* LaunchAgents I created (but they're needed for the system)\n2. Rename them to not start with \"ai.openclaw.\"\n3. Ignore the warnings (gateway is actually running fine)\n\nLooking at the logs, the gateway IS running. The warnings are just warnings, not actual crashes. Let me check if the gateway is actually crashing or if it's just showing warnings.\n\nLet me fix this by renaming the LaunchAgents to not conflict with the gateway naming scheme.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0d9892511b9e4abe93841c6f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# The gateway is warning about LaunchAgents with \"ai.openclaw.\" prefix\n# Rename them to avoid false conflicts\nmv /Users/kublai/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.heartbeat-watchdog.plist /Users/kublai/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kurultai.heartbeat-watchdog.plist 2>/dev/null\nmv /Users/kublai/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.spawn-consumer.plist /Users/kublai/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kurultai.spawn-consumer.plist 2>/dev/null\n\n# Reload the renamed LaunchAgents\nlaunchctl unload /Users/kublai/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kurultai.heartbeat-watchdog.plist 2>/dev/null; launchctl load /Users/kublai/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kurultai.heartbeat-watchdog.plist 2>/dev/null\nlaunchctl unload /Users/kublai/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kurultai.spawn-consumer.plist 2>/dev/null; launchctl load /Users/kublai/Library/LaunchAgents/com.kurultai.spawn-consumer.plist 2>/dev/null\n\n# Restart gateway\nopenclaw gateway restart 2>&1 | head -3\nsleep 2\nopenclaw gateway status 2>&1 | grep -E \"Runtime:|running|Listening\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":437057,"output":786,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":437843,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772585014698}}
