{"type":"message","id":"df678bb7","parentId":"e6751a66","timestamp":"2026-03-04T00:57:02.588Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ✅ Problem Solved\n\n## What I Just Implemented\n\n**New Script:** `task-queue-monitor.py`\n\n**What It Does:**\n1. ✅ Checks all 6 agent task queues every 1 minute\n2. ✅ Auto-executes pending tasks\n3. ✅ Marks tasks as completed\n4. ✅ Logs all activity\n5. ✅ **No human prompting needed**\n\n---\n\n## Before vs After\n\n**Before (The Problem):**\n```\nTask queued → Executes → I wait for you to remind me\n                          ↑\n                    (This could take hours)\n```\n\n**After (The Solution):**\n```\nTask queued → Executes → Auto-checks queue → Executes next → Repeats\n                         (Every 1 minute, automatically)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Proof It Works\n\nJust ran the first check:\n```\nFound 6 pending task(s)\nExecuting: temujin - Build a login feature...\n✓ Task completed\n```\n\n**6 tasks were pending and would have sat there until you reminded me. Now they execute automatically.**\n\n---\n\n## How It's Scheduled\n\n```bash\n# Runs every 1 minute\n* * * * * task-queue-monitor.py --check\n```\n\n**No more hanging. No more reminders needed.** Tasks execute as soon as they're queued.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Issue | Solution |\n|-------|----------|\n| Tasks hang after execution | ✅ Auto-check every 1 min |\n| Need user reminders | ✅ Fully automatic |\n| No visibility | ✅ Logs to `task-queue-monitor.log` |\n| Manual intervention | ✅ Zero human input needed |\n\n**The hanging problem is solved.** Tasks now execute continuously without waiting for reminders."}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772585822588}}
