{"type":"message","id":"40b3a44e","parentId":"2d09f77e","timestamp":"2026-03-04T01:04:35.457Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is reporting two issues:\n\n1. **Gateway showing \"disconnected (1006)\" for ~1 second every 15 seconds** - This is a WebSocket disconnection/reconnection cycle happening repeatedly. Error 1006 is a WebSocket abnormal closure code.\n\n2. **No response issue** - When I run long exec commands, they timeout and no response gets sent back to the user.\n\nLet me investigate both issues.\n\nFor issue #1, I need to check:\n- Gateway logs for WebSocket disconnect reasons\n- LaunchAgent configuration\n- Network/port conflicts\n- Resource issues\n\nFor issue #2, I need to:\n- Use shorter commands\n- Add timeouts to exec commands\n- Implement fallback responses\n- Maybe use a different approach for diagnostics\n\nLet me start investigating.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5dab047d6eb54ddc950988a6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check gateway logs for WebSocket disconnects\necho \"=== Gateway WebSocket Logs ===\" && tail -50 /Users/kublai/.openclaw/logs/openclaw.log 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"websocket\\|1006\\|disconnect\\|close\\|reconnect\" | tail -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":451519,"output":434,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":451953,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772586258925}}
